linux-cachyos-surface-latest
=============================

This repository's git history is seeded from linux-surface/linux-surface (it
is not a GitHub-tracked Fork of that repo only because GitHub allows just one
fork per source repo per account, and that slot is used by the sibling
project github.com/Steefzar/linux-cachyos-surface -- the content and history
base are the same). It adds a CachyOS kernel packaging
(`pkg/linux-cachyos-surface-latest/PKGBUILD`) that tracks the newest CachyOS
kernel release, rather than whatever version linux-surface's official patches
currently support.

When linux-surface's official patches already cover the target kernel's major
version, this builds identically to `linux-cachyos-surface`. When there's a
version gap, it falls back to a hand-rebased patch set bundled in
`pkg/linux-cachyos-surface-latest/` (see `STATUS` there for what it was last
validated against). That fallback is
best-effort: if it stops applying cleanly against a newer kernel, the build
aborts with a clear message rather than silently shipping something broken,
and a fresh rebase (manual, or with Claude's help as before) is needed.

Credit and thanks:

  - linux-surface/linux-surface (https://github.com/linux-surface/linux-surface)
    -- GPL-2.0. Every Surface hardware-enablement patch this kernel carries,
